The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 30 September is 76,659 (8,835.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 September, there were 2,290 new confirmed cases (263.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 September, there were 1,550 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 48% (740 extra cases).
